Subject: Aircraft receives start up approval
Source Text: Definition ASAT - Actual start up Approval Time. This is the time that an aircraft receives its start up approval.

Subject: Aircraft starts up, pushes back, taxis
Source Text: Effect On receipt of ATC approval, the aircraft will start up, push back and start to taxi.

Subject: Aircraft starts up, pushes back, taxis
Source Text: Effect On receipt of ATC approval, the aircraft will start up, push back and start to taxi.

Subject: Inform partners of ASAT in ACISP
Source Text: First step: To inform all relevant Airport CDM Partners of Actual start up approval Time (ASAT) in the Airport CDM Platform and that the aircraft has received start up approval / push-back clearance.

Subject: Check ASAT vs TSAT
Source Text: Second step: To check if ASAT is in accordance to TSAT and to alert all relevant Airport CDM Partners when no start up has been granted.

Subject: Alert partners if no start up granted
Source Text: Second step: To check if ASAT is in accordance to TSAT and to alert all relevant Airport CDM Partners when no start up has been granted.

Subject: Inform partners if start up not granted at TSAT + tolerance
Source Text: In case the start up approval is not granted at TSAT + tolerance, all relevant partners should be informed.
